contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|sina}} '''Sina''' may refer to: * [[Chin (China)]], or Sina (Chinese 支那), old Chinese form of the Sanskrit name Cina (चीन) ** [[Shina (word)]], or Sina (Japanese 支那), old Japanese word for China ** [[Sinae]], Latin name for China * [[Sina Corp]] (新浪), Chinese company and website * [[Sina, Albania]], or Sinë, village in Dibër County, Albania * [[Sina, Iran]], a village in Bushehr Province, Iran * [[Sina District]], in San Antonio de Putina Province, Peru * "Sina", a song by Brazilian singer [[Djavan]] * "Soulfood To Go (Sina)", English title of a cover of this song by [[Manhattan Transfer (band)]] * [[Sina and the Eel]], a Samoan myth of origin * ''[[Sina-1]]'', an Iranian satellite launched on a Russian rocket in October 2005 * [[Sina 7 (frigate)|''Sina 7'' (frigate)]], an Iranian frigate launched on Nov 2012 * [[Sina class]], designation of the [[Iranian missile boat Paykan]] * [[Sina Bank]], a private Iranian bank ;SINA * [[Society for Indecency to Naked Animals]], a hoax perpetuated by Alan Abel ;People *[[Ibn Sīnā]] (c. 980 – 1037), Avicenna, a Persian physician, philosopher, and scientist *[[Elvis Sina]] (born 1978), an Albanian footballer *[[Nasser Sina]] (born 1962), a Kurdish veteran and journalist *[[Than Sina]], Cambodian politician *[[Sina Ashouri]] (born 1988), an Iranian footballer *[[Ali Sina (activist)]], pseudonym of the founder of Faith Freedom International, a secularist website with critiques of Islam ==See also== *[[Sino (disambiguation)]] ** [[:wikt:Sino-|Sino-]] prefix from Latin meaning China- {{disambiguation}}
